


TimeEngine — Observer‑Dependent Information Geometry Over CMS Heavy‑Ion Data
Author: David E. Blackwell
Data: CMS Heavy‑Ion D⁰ Photoproduction (HEPData)
Engine: ODIM → Observer Metrics → Clocks → Geodesics → Horizons → Embeddings → Stress Tests

Overview
TimeEngine is a full information‑geometric pipeline that constructs:

Observer‑dependent time flows

Physical clocks (yield‑based + experimental)

Local curvature tensors

Discrete + continuous geodesics

2D + 3D manifold embeddings

Observer‑dependent horizons

Divergence matrices

Time‑curvature tensors

Phase‑2 stress tests (noise storms + metric sweeps)

Everything is built from real CMS D⁰ cross‑section tables.

This repository contains:

The full ODIM engine

The V2 time engine

Phase‑2 stress suite

All outputs, plots, and diagnostic CSVs

📌 Pipeline Structure
There are two main stages, plus an optional Phase‑2 stress suite.

Stage 1 — Data Processing (Run FIRST)
This stage converts raw CMS CSVs into ODIM‑ready data.

